                    // If a[i] is positive, it adds to this balance.
                    // If a[i] is negative, it consumes from this balance.
                    // If the balance becomes negative, it means we need to "pull"
                    // value from some j > i to satisfy the deficit up to i.
                    // This "pulling" operation (j to i, j > i) is free.
                    // The cost is incurred when we move from i to j where i > j.
                    // This means we are moving a positive value from a later index
                    // to an earlier index.
