        //   We must move X <= h_i. To cover p_filtered[current_p_idx], X must be <= p_filtered[current_p_idx].
        //   The furthest right we can reach is h_i.
        //   The furthest left we can reach is h_i - T.
        //   So we can move to any X in [h_i - T, h_i].
        //   To cover p_filtered[current_p_idx], we need X <= p_filtered[current_p_idx].
        //   So we can move to any X in [h_i - T, min(h_i, p_filtered[current_p_idx])].
        //   The interval covered is [X, h_i].
        //   To maximize the rightmost point covered, we want to maximize h_i. This is fixed.
        //   This logic is flawed. The head moves to X. It covers [min(h_i, X), max(h_i, X)].
