        //     The rightmost point covered is max(h_i, p_filtered[current_p_idx]).
        //     This is not enough. We want to cover as many subsequent p's as possible.
        //     If we move to X, we cover [min(h_i, X), max(h_i, X)].
        //     The time taken is |h_i - X|.
        //     The remaining time is T - |h_i - X|.
        //     With this remaining time, we can extend the interval.
        //     If X < h_i, we can extend to [X - remaining_time, h_i + remaining_time].
        //     If X > h_i, we can extend to [h_i - remaining_time, X + remaining_time].
        //     If X = h_i, we can extend to [h_i - remaining_time, h_i + remaining_time].
        //     This is equivalent to saying the head can cover any point Y such that |h_i - Y| <= T.
